This paper deals with image retrieval in the fashion domain, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves graph reasoning and message passing, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). The paper also involves similarity learning, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of graph convolutional networks also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text-based retrieval, which suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
